Compares two strings, returning a true response if and only if they contain the same sequence of characters. A null string is considered to be equal to an empty string.

Inputs\:
string1 - The first string.
string2 - The second string.
ignoreCase - If set to 'true', then the comparison ignores case considerations. The two strings are considered equal ignoring case if they are of the same length and corresponding characters in the two strings are equal ignoring case. If set to any value other than 'true', then the strings must match exactly to be considered equal.

responses\:
true - If the two strings are equal
false - If the two strings are not equal

a89c78d0-3f1c-4839-a466-1192c816c518.description=
Synopsis

    This flow sets the volume configuration for a Unified Storage LUN volume.
    setSusLunRwVolConfig performs the following steps\:
      1. Retrieve the vServer based on the required inputs using the HPOO flow getVserver.
      2. Determine that a vServer with the determined parameters exists.
      3. Retrieve the volume details.
      4. Determine that a volume with the determined parameters exists.
      5. Retrieve the NAS volume API configurations.
      6. Modify the volume attributes.
      7. Set the volume options.
      8. Set the snapshot autodelete options.
      9. Determine whether to enable single-instance storage (SIS).
    10. Set the volume SIS configuration.
    11. Set the configuration for the volume hybrid cache.
    12. Set the configuration for the volume autosize.
    13. Pass the information back to the requesting entity.

Inputs

    clusterName - The IP or host name of the NetApp cluster (required).
      Valid values\: Dot-decimal notation IPv4 address or RFC 1123 compliant host name.
      Default value\: None.

    vServerName - The name of the vServer used in the flow (required).
    volumeName - The name of the volume used in the flow (required).
    volumeTypeFs - The type of volume that is configured. Volume type is based on the rules and permissions surrounding the volume (required).
    protocol - The protocol of the volume (CIFS, NAS, etc.). A protocol relates to the operating system utilized in storage deployment (required).
    storageTier - The tier of storage (e.g. Vital, Velocity, or Value) (required).
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: None.

    overrideJRAS - Value to override the system-defined Java RAS server.
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: Hosting Eng RAS.

Results

    hpooFlowResult - The XML response specific to the functionality of the flow; in this case, a volume configuration for a LUN. See Notes section for more details.
    flowStatus - Overall status of the flow, value is one of the string literals "success" or "failed".

Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
    Failure - Some operations and/or subflows failed.

Notes

    1. Anything else the caller or support person may need to know about the flow. Relationships that aren't easily inferred, abmnormal flow behaviors, hard-codings, etc.
